id: pm-iqq0
title: "Declarative extension authoring: composeExtension blueprint + deriveExtensionCapabilities + defineExtensionManifest"
description: "Capstone of the SDK authoring tripod (author -> register -> test). Today every package author hand-wires each api.register* call inside an imperative activate(api) and hand-syncs manifest.capabilities, which is the two biggest package-authoring footguns (forgotten/mis-ordered registration; over- or under-declared capabilities). This adds a declarative authoring surface so an author (or agent) describes WHAT to register as data and the SDK generates the correct activate:\n\n1. composeExtension(blueprint): ExtensionModule — accepts arrays/records of define*-authored definitions (commands, commandOverrides, flags, parsers, renderers, services, preflights, itemTypes, itemFields, migrations, searchProviders, vectorStoreAdapters, importers, exporters, the 5 hook kinds) plus optional manifest/activate/deactivate, and returns a module whose generated activate calls every api.register* in a deterministic order, then runs any explicit imperative activate. Pure assembler; validation stays in register* (ADR pm-3mph).\n2. deriveExtensionCapabilities(blueprint): ExtensionCapability[] — author-time inverse of reconcileExtensionCapabilityUsage (pm-fk84): computes the minimal least-privilege capability set a blueprint exercises, so manifest.json capabilities can be authored exactly with no declared-but-unused / used-but-undeclared drift. Mapping mirrors EXTENSION_CAPABILITY_REGISTRATION_SURFACES (flags/itemTypes/itemFields/migrations -> schema, etc).\n3. defineExtensionManifest(manifest): ExtensionManifest — completes the define* identity family (the manifest was the one authoring surface without a builder); types the in-module manifest mirror.\n\nArchitecture: move ExtensionModule + defineExtension into the new src/sdk/compose.ts (no import cycle; re-exported from the barrel so the public API is unchanged). NOT dogfooded into the bundled first-party packages because those are intentionally import-free for extension-only installs; demonstrated in docs/SDK.md + tests instead, targeting npm package-mode authors who depend on the SDK. 100% test + docstring coverage; SDK.md Declarative Authoring section."
type: Feature
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[3]: "area:extensions","area:packages","area:sdk"
