author: claude-code-agent
parent: pm-ugqx
resolution: "Delivered composeExtension + deriveExtensionCapabilities + defineExtensionManifest as the declarative-authoring capstone of the SDK author->register->test loop; 100% coverage/docstrings, all gates green, smoke-verified through the built bundle and the real pm CLI."
expected_result: "Package authors (and agents) can author an extension declaratively: composeExtension(blueprint) generates the activate that wires every api.register* surface, deriveExtensionCapabilities(blueprint) yields the exact least-privilege manifest capability set, and defineExtensionManifest types the manifest mirror. Public SDK API unchanged; 100% coverage + docstrings; all gates green."
actual_result: "Delivered exactly that. composeExtension + deriveExtensionCapabilities (src/sdk/compose.ts) + defineExtensionManifest (src/sdk/define.ts), ExtensionModule/defineExtension relocated and re-exported from the barrel. 4872 tests at 100% coverage, typecheck/static/docs/contracts gates green, and verified end-to-end through both the built bundle and a real pm CLI subprocess (extension loaded, described, dispatched; package doctor clean)."
