comments[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-22T21:09:08.622Z",claude-code-agent,"PR #346 review round 1 — addressed and pushed. Gemini (4 findings, all the same REAL null-robustness theme): composeExtension and deriveExtensionCapabilities now treat an explicit null (optional field or hooks) like undefined instead of throwing (Object.keys(null) / null-hooks deref) — hasEntries uses !value, hooks use `?? {}` (Gemini's literal `hooks !== null` suggestion would not compile since null is not in the type). Added an explicit-null robustness unit test. CodeRabbit (2 findings): (1) REAL docstring over-claim — defineExtensionManifest does NOT preserve a `capabilities` tuple literal (ExtensionManifest.capabilities is string[]; only `as const` would), reworded define.ts + SDK.md to the accurate contract-checking value; (2) trivial SDK.md `exactly` repetition reworded. Sourcery rate-limited (weekly cap); Codex not connected. Re-verified: 4872 tests 100% coverage, typecheck/static/docs gates green. Re-triggering bots for round 2."
learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-22T20:48:27.250Z",claude-code-agent,"deriveExtensionCapabilities and composeExtension agree with the loader BY CONSTRUCTION: the field->capability table mirrors EXTENSION_CAPABILITY_REGISTRATION_SURFACES (registerFlags/registerItemFields/registerItemTypes/registerMigration all -> schema, NOT commands; registerImporter/registerExporter -> importers; search providers + vector adapters -> search). Verified end-to-end: a full blueprint activated with exactly its derived capabilities produces zero capability-missing failures. composeExtension is a pure assembler with no validation (ADR pm-3mph) - per-surface contract enforcement stays in api.register*. defineExtension/ExtensionModule were relocated from index.ts into compose.ts (type-only ExtensionCapability import from loader.js, no import cycle) and re-exported from the barrel, so the public API is unchanged. The bundled first-party packages deliberately keep import-free hand-written activate bodies (so they load in extension-only installs without SDK module resolution), so composeExtension is documented for npm package-mode authors, NOT dogfooded into the bundled exemplars."
