close_reason: "Shipped declarative extension authoring on branch feat/sdk-declarative-compose-extension. New src/sdk/compose.ts exports composeExtension(blueprint)->ExtensionModule (generates an activate that wires every populated surface via api.register* in deterministic order, then awaits an optional imperative activate escape hatch), deriveExtensionCapabilities(blueprint)->least-privilege capability set, and the relocated ExtensionModule + defineExtension (re-exported from the barrel; public API unchanged). define.ts gains defineExtensionManifest, completing the define* identity family. docs/SDK.md adds a Declarative Authoring section. Verified: full suite 4872 tests 100% coverage (stmts/branch/funcs/lines), typecheck (both tsconfigs) clean, static + docs-skills + contracts gates green. Manual temp-dir smoke: built-bundle E2E (deriveExtensionCapabilities->[commands,schema], activation 0 failures with exactly the derived caps, command dispatched) AND real pm CLI subprocess (extension loaded from <pmRoot>/extensions, pm extension describe reflects it, pm <cmd> dispatched, pm package doctor clean activation with 0 capability/consistency warnings). Not dogfooded into bundled packages (they stay import-free for extension-only installs)."
